sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant B as Browser
    participant API as FastAPI
    participant Q as Celery Queue
    participant W as Celery Worker
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    participant S3 as AWS S3
    participant WS as WebSocket

    Note over B,WS: Async export generation (all format types)
    B->>+API: POST /api/v1/exports {tree_id, format:PDF, options:{generations:5}}
    API->>API: Validate quota (exports/month per tier)
    API->>DB: INSERT INTO exports (tenant_id, tree_id, format, status=QUEUED)
    DB-->>API: export_id
    API->>Q: enqueue generate_export(export_id, format=PDF, options)
    API-->>-B: 202 Accepted {export_id, status:QUEUED, poll_url, ws_channel}

    Note over W,S3: Worker processes export (background)
    Q->>W: generate_export(export_id)
    W->>DB: SELECT export, tree, persons (recursive CTE for N generations)
    DB-->>W: tree data (potentially 10,000+ profiles)
    W->>W: Build in-memory tree graph

    alt format = GEDCOM
        W->>W: Serialize to GEDCOM 5.5.1 spec
    else format = PDF Tree
        W->>W: Render SVG via D3 layout engine (headless)
        W->>W: Convert SVG → PDF (WeasyPrint / ReportLab)
    else format = PNG Tree
        W->>W: Render SVG → rasterize PNG at 300 DPI
    else format = Narrative Report
        W->>W: Generate prose narrative per generation
        W->>W: Render PDF with citations (ReportLab)
    end

    W->>S3: PUT exports/{tenant_id}/{export_id}.{ext} (presigned, 24h TTL)
    W->>DB: UPDATE exports SET status=READY, s3_key=..., expires_at=...
    W->>Q: enqueue notify_export_ready(export_id)

    Note over WS,B: Real-time notification (no polling needed)
    W->>WS: PUBLISH ws:user:{user_id} {type:export_ready, export_id, download_url}
    WS-->>B: {type:export_ready, download_url}
    B->>S3: GET {download_url} (presigned, one-time)
    S3-->>B: file download
